        <section id="why" class="feature-list">
            <div class="column column-one">
                <div  class="pages">
                    <h3><i class="fa fa-database"></i> Projects</h3>
                    Section dedicated to the management of your projects and those created by others.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a href="#project/newproject"><h4><i class="fa fa-plus"></i> New project</h4></a>
                    It gives you the ability to create new projects and to describe them.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a href="#project/openproject"><h4><i class="fa fa-folder-open"></i> Open project</h4></a>
                    List of all projects created in BigDataManager by all users from which you can open one to display its statistics.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a href="#project/editproject"><h4><i class="fa fa-pencil"></i> Edit project</h4></a>
                    It allows you to edit the information of your project, insert data inside the project,
                    synchronize data with the regions contained in the database, manage eventual tags and tokens.
                </div>


            </div>

            <div class="column column-two">
                <div class="pages">
                    <h3><i class="fa fa-cogs"></i> Database</h3>
                    Section reserved for system administrators to change the database information globally.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a ng-if="isAdmin()" href="#/db/users"><h4><i class="fa fa-user-plus"></i> Users</h4></a>
                    <div ng-if="!isAdmin()" ><h4><i class="fa fa-user-plus"></i> Users</h4></div>
                    List of registered users.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a ng-if="isAdmin()" href="#/db/nations"><h4><i class="fa fa-folder-open"></i> Nations</h4></a>
                    <div ng-if="!isAdmin()" href="#/db/nations"><h4><i class="fa fa-folder-open"></i> Nations</h4></div>
                    List of European nations already entered into the database necessary for geo-localization data.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a ng-if="isAdmin()" href="#/db/normalization"><h4><i class="fa fa-balance-scale"></i> Normalization</h4></a>
                    <div ng-if="!isAdmin()" href="#/db/normalization"><h4><i class="fa fa-balance-scale"></i> Normalization</h4></div>
                    Normalization data
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="column column-three">
                <div class="pages">
                    <h3><i class="fa fa-bar-chart"></i> Statistics</h3>
                    Section that allows you to to display different types of statistics on data of the selected project.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a href="#stat/showdata"><h4><i class="fa fa-table"></i> Show data</h4></a>
                    It displays the raw data of the project with the ability to filter them for fields.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a href="#stat/showmap"><h4><i class="fa fa-map-marker"></i> Show map</h4></a>
                    It shows only the georeferenced data on the map in accordance with appropriate filters.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a href="#stat/compare"><h4><i class="fa fa-exchange"></i> Compare</h4></a>
                    Bar chart or radar chart for comparison between nations or regions on the basis of their data.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a href="#stat/timeline"><h4><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> Timeline</h4></a>
                    It shows the time trend of the data filterable by tags or users.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a href="#stat/showtag"><h4><i class="fa fa-cloud"></i> Word cloud</h4></a>
                    It shows the word cloud of tokens and bar charts that show the occurrences of the tags and tokens.
                </div>
                <div class="pages">
                    <a href="#stat/showusers"><h4><i class="fa fa-group"></i> User statistics</h4></a>
                    It allows you to view detailed statistics of users.
                </div>
            </div>
